{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:45:39.542400+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture of the repository. Let me analyze the issue:\n\n**Issue #1**: \"Fix a broken getting-started link\" — the issue asks to fix a broken link in the MkDocs getting-started page and keep the site navigation valid.\n\nLooking at the repository structure:\n- `docs/getting-started.md` has a link to `configuration.md` ✅ (exists)\n- `docs/index.md` has a link to `getting-started.md` ✅ (exists)\n- `mkdocs.yml` nav lists pages but is **missing** `docs/troubleshooting.md` which exists in the repo\n\nThe `mkdocs.yml` nav does not include `troubleshooting.md`, even though the file exists. The `getting-started.md` page also doesn't reference troubleshooting. This is the broken navigation — a page exists but isn't accessible through the site nav.\n\nLet me fix the `mkdocs.yml` to include the missing `troubleshooting.md` page in the navigation:", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 7984, "prompt_tokens": 9342, "total_tokens": 17326, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 7546, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0071997252, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002536452, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00694608}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780983749-pLH1ur4pS0Dkuoi6pRQN", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaae7-57fa-7510-8fc1-5d81b9f22162-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "create_or_update_file", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T16_R01_C01_A02", "branch": "